rComments: I agree with the person before - Prof Mohan's brutal, but in a good way. She is a hard marker but she spends tons of time marking your work individually and giving you feedback. And then you feel pretty bad that you didn't write better. Plus she makes studying theory totally worth it.

This was a great course and I loved the literature readings. I didnt know anything about the Tamil issue until this course. Loved her sense of humor ("Paris Hilton as feminist"?!!) Plus, Mohan doesnt bell curve - who wont love that!
Amazing course, anyone should take it.

Prof Mohan is a hard taskmaster but that's a good thing in a university where everyone's busy churning out an average. She loves her subject and makes you love it too! One of the most theoretically challenging courses I took and though I didn't get the grade I want (lots of personal issues), I still recommend her courses highly!
This class was a great class. I had a good time taking it. It was very interesting and easy to learn. I 100% recommend this class for anyone from any post.

This professor is great to listen to and enthusiastic about her class. Definitely a fun and interesting class. She is very helpful and easy to understand. I totally recommend this class for anyone from any background.
